  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_3' aria-label=\" Hitesh Nagjibhai Patel versus Bababhai Nagjibhai Rabari & Anr. pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('3','2025','2025_8_2428_2436','2025INSC1070'); ><font size='4'> <strong>HITESH NAGJIBHAI PATEL<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>BABABHAI NAGJIBHAI RABARI & ANR. </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 8 S.C.R. 2428</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 1070</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010008602025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : SANJAY KAROL, PRASHANT KUMAR MISHRA</strong><br> Issue for Consideration Issue arose whether the courts below failed to award compensation under the head loss of earnings to the minor appellant; and whether the High Court erred in granting an adequate amount of compensation under pecuniary and non-pecuniary damages. Headnotes&dagger; &ndash; Compensation &ndash; Enhancement &ndash; Appellant-minor aged 8 years suffered permanent disability in a road accident &ndash; Tribunal awarded compensation of Rs. 3.90 lakh &ndash; High Court enhanced it to Rs. 8.65 lakhs &ndash; Interference: Held: Minor child who suffers death or<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 08-08-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CIVIL APPEAL No. 10278/2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Appeal(s) allowed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('3','2025','2025_8_2428_2436','2025INSC1070','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split view</a></div><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitv